WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.004
<i>♪ MTV ♪</i>

00:06.807 --> 00:09.309
[Jacob]
<i>I've been here since 1894.</i>

00:09.310 --> 00:11.579
My concern is survival.

00:11.679 --> 00:13.114
You're no God, Jacob Dutton!

00:13.214 --> 00:15.183
[Cara]
<i>Spencer, this ranch</i>

00:15.283 --> 00:17.150
<i>and your legacy are in peril.</i>

00:17.151 --> 00:20.020
<i>You must come home
and fight this war.</i>

00:20.154 --> 00:21.589
[Alex]
<i>You're a hunter.</i>

00:21.689 --> 00:23.023
[roars]

00:23.124 --> 00:24.525
<i>Where does the next
adventure take you?</i>

00:24.625 --> 00:25.659
Where I'm going is dangerous.

00:25.759 --> 00:27.695
[Alex]
<i>Let's look</i>

00:27.795 --> 00:29.363
death in the eye, then,
shall we?

00:29.463 --> 00:31.799
- [yelling]
- [screams]

00:31.899 --> 00:33.367
<i>♪ rousing music ♪</i>

00:33.634 --> 00:35.403
<i>***</i>

00:40.374 --> 00:41.542
[Sister Alice]
<i>I've sworn</i>

00:41.675 --> 00:42.710
to kill the Indian in you

00:42.843 --> 00:44.745
<i>and will keep my word.</i>

00:44.845 --> 00:46.247
What are you doing?

00:46.380 --> 00:47.781
Making war.

00:49.450 --> 00:52.353
[Renaud] <i>I have compassion
but I have no mercy.</i>

00:52.453 --> 00:53.721
Bring her back to me.

00:53.821 --> 00:56.590
I want the whole valley.

00:56.690 --> 00:59.160
I'm a man of my word!

01:00.594 --> 01:02.396
Aah!

01:04.598 --> 01:06.400
- You need to read this.
- You read it.

01:06.534 --> 01:08.701
"War has descended
upon this place."

01:08.702 --> 01:10.537
[Cara]
<i>I fear everything your parents</i>

01:10.538 --> 01:11.905
<i>fought so hard to build</i>

01:12.039 --> 01:13.441
<i>is being ripped from us.</i>

01:13.574 --> 01:16.210
[Spencer] <i>I need
to book passage to America.</i>

01:16.310 --> 01:18.078
I do not yield, you Yankee scum!

01:18.179 --> 01:19.580
[screams]

01:19.680 --> 01:21.782
[Hurley]
Take this man to the brig.

01:21.882 --> 01:23.884
- Spencer!
- I love you, Alex!

01:23.984 --> 01:26.420
I will come to you!

01:33.894 --> 01:35.663
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

01:35.929 --> 01:38.132
<i>***</i>

01:47.841 --> 01:49.643
<i>♪ pastoral music ♪</i>

01:49.977 --> 01:52.112
<i>***</i>

02:14.067 --> 02:15.703
[Cara]
<i>Dear Spencer...</i>

02:16.804 --> 02:18.939
<i>...we have sold
the last of our herd,</i>

02:19.039 --> 02:20.874
<i>keeping only four bulls</i>

02:20.974 --> 02:23.109
<i>and 100 heifers,</i>

02:23.110 --> 02:24.411
<i>the seeds with which</i>

02:24.412 --> 02:25.979
<i>you must rebuild the ranch</i>

02:26.079 --> 02:27.414
<i>that trickery</i>

02:27.415 --> 02:29.650
<i>and laws drafted by loan sharks</i>

02:29.783 --> 02:31.852
<i>have stripped from us.</i>

02:39.159 --> 02:41.829
<i>The road to Bozeman
is snowed over now,</i>

02:41.929 --> 02:44.031
<i>passable only on horseback.</i>

02:44.865 --> 02:46.834
<i>Our movement is restricted
to the lodge</i>

02:46.934 --> 02:50.371
<i>and the pastures
around the barn until spring.</i>

03:07.221 --> 03:09.357
<i>***</i>

03:22.736 --> 03:26.240
<i>We dare not kill a beef,
so the men hunt.</i>

03:27.207 --> 03:29.710
<i>Gone are the great feasts
of summer.</i>

03:29.843 --> 03:30.944
<i>It is stews</i>

03:31.044 --> 03:32.645
<i>and stale bread</i>

03:32.646 --> 03:35.449
<i>and the bland fuel
of sustenance.</i>

03:35.549 --> 03:36.649
<i>Like the bear,</i>

03:36.650 --> 03:38.651
<i>we hibernate,</i>

03:38.652 --> 03:42.756
<i>impatiently awaiting spring
and your return.</i>

04:05.513 --> 04:07.315
What time is the hearing?

04:07.415 --> 04:09.249
First thing in the morning.

04:09.350 --> 04:11.552
I'll be back tomorrow night.

04:11.652 --> 04:13.554
Don't kill yourself racing
back to me in a blizzard.

04:13.654 --> 04:15.423
If there's a blizzard,

04:15.523 --> 04:18.358
I'll ride it out
in the comfort of the hotel.

04:18.359 --> 04:21.161
[chuckles] You mean
the speakeasy beneath it?

04:21.261 --> 04:23.831
That's exactly what I mean.

04:28.035 --> 04:31.305
[Cara] You know the Parkers
in Livingston?

04:31.405 --> 04:32.906
I know the Parkers.

04:33.006 --> 04:35.443
Mary Parker told me they have
a telephone in their house.

04:35.543 --> 04:36.610
In her house.

04:36.744 --> 04:37.945
Can you imagine?

04:38.045 --> 04:39.413
When Albert goes to Bozeman,

04:39.513 --> 04:42.214
he can stop by the telegram
office and for a nickel,

04:42.215 --> 04:43.884
he can call Mary at her house

04:43.984 --> 04:46.387
so she knows he got there safe.

04:46.487 --> 04:48.356
Yeah, with Albert's
sense of direction,

04:48.456 --> 04:49.890
that seems like a good plan.

04:49.990 --> 04:51.391
Well, no, uh, you know,
I'm just saying,

04:51.392 --> 04:54.260
would be nice to know
that you got there safe

04:54.261 --> 04:56.330
instead of hoping
you made it safe

04:56.430 --> 04:58.499
and wondering and worrying.

04:58.632 --> 04:59.900
Well, if you weren't
worrying about me,

05:00.000 --> 05:01.469
you'd be worrying
about something else.

05:01.569 --> 05:03.671
Yes, but that would be
a worry of my own choosing.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.606
- [sighs]
- Not one that you chose for me.

05:06.607 --> 05:09.677
This trip is not a choice.
It's a duty.

05:09.777 --> 05:12.513
So I'm just gonna say
I will not allow today

05:12.613 --> 05:15.483
to be the last time
I see your face.

05:16.283 --> 05:17.851
Thank you.

05:18.686 --> 05:20.087
I'll see you tomorrow.

05:24.792 --> 05:28.161
- Whoa! Whoa!
- [neighing]

05:28.261 --> 05:29.697
They're fresh this morning.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.665
[soft growling nearby]

05:31.765 --> 05:33.734
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

05:33.834 --> 05:37.170
Take those horses down the hill.
I'll meet you at the barn.

05:37.270 --> 05:38.739
Back to the barn?

05:38.839 --> 05:41.474
- There's a lion on the porch.
- A lion?

05:41.475 --> 05:43.276
Yeah.

05:43.377 --> 05:44.945
Come on, go.

05:45.045 --> 05:46.380
Get.

05:47.981 --> 05:49.983
Look here,

05:50.083 --> 05:51.151
I don't want to shoot you

05:51.251 --> 05:54.120
and you don't want to get shot.

05:54.121 --> 05:55.287
I need to know,

05:55.288 --> 05:57.024
are you up here to get warm

05:57.124 --> 05:58.157
or are you

05:58.158 --> 06:00.728
hunting your next meal?

06:13.006 --> 06:14.542
What you doing?

06:15.409 --> 06:16.877
Why are you standing
on the porch

06:16.977 --> 06:19.880
- scowling at the mountains?
- Hmm.

06:23.517 --> 06:25.252
It was just here.

06:25.352 --> 06:27.555
It wasn't after us.

06:30.858 --> 06:32.492
Well, that's comforting.

06:32.493 --> 06:35.663
Now you have something
to worry about as well.

06:37.397 --> 06:40.133
I'm always worried, honey.

07:08.929 --> 07:10.530
- Got kerosene?
- Yes, sir.

07:10.531 --> 07:12.099
Matches?

07:12.199 --> 07:13.801
Ain't much good without 'em.

07:33.987 --> 07:35.823
<i>♪ majestic orchestral music ♪</i>

07:36.156 --> 07:38.291
<i>***</i>

08:08.121 --> 08:10.290
<i>***</i>

08:27.841 --> 08:30.043
<i>***</i>

08:47.327 --> 08:49.096
<i>♪ pensive music ♪</i>

08:49.362 --> 08:51.565
<i>***</i>

09:09.416 --> 09:11.885
[chuckling]

09:11.985 --> 09:14.087
What's funny?

09:14.187 --> 09:16.223
A certain trial starts tomorrow.

09:16.323 --> 09:17.958
Trial about what?

09:19.292 --> 09:20.560
Did you know that the honey bee

09:20.661 --> 09:22.062
kills more people each year

09:22.162 --> 09:23.897
than the rattlesnake?

09:25.332 --> 09:27.635
More than the grizzly?

09:28.501 --> 09:30.771
It's the accumulation
of thousands

09:30.871 --> 09:34.541
of little stings
which killed the bee as well,

09:34.642 --> 09:37.077
I might add.

09:37.210 --> 09:40.080
They sacrifice themselves.

09:41.815 --> 09:45.819
The trial's just
another little sting.

10:01.034 --> 10:02.703
[chuckles softly]

10:09.977 --> 10:12.813
I think we should
bring our little doll

10:12.946 --> 10:14.715
out to play.

10:15.615 --> 10:18.819
Don't you think?
Would you like that?

10:18.952 --> 10:21.321
[gasping softly] Yes.

10:23.190 --> 10:24.825
Go get her.

10:25.759 --> 10:28.128
Go on, get her.

10:36.770 --> 10:39.807
No need to dry off.

10:40.507 --> 10:43.143
I rather prefer you wet.

10:48.548 --> 10:49.750
[door opens]

10:49.850 --> 10:51.751
<i>♪ sinister music ♪</i>

10:51.752 --> 10:54.487
<i>***</i>

11:03.931 --> 11:05.598
Wake up.

11:12.205 --> 11:13.907
[whimpers softly]

11:27.420 --> 11:29.189
Look at me.

11:39.032 --> 11:40.700
You only get punished

11:40.801 --> 11:43.303
if you don't try hard.

11:44.204 --> 11:46.106
That's all.

11:51.845 --> 11:54.481
But if you try...

11:54.581 --> 11:57.584
really hard...

11:59.386 --> 12:01.188
...we'll give you a surprise.

12:23.210 --> 12:24.710
Where do you think you're going?

12:24.711 --> 12:26.579
I thought I'd go to town
with you.

12:26.679 --> 12:27.847
Stay with your mother.

12:27.848 --> 12:30.717
There's nothing
to do in Livingston.

12:30.818 --> 12:33.253
There's nothing to do
in Bozeman either.

12:33.353 --> 12:36.423
It's below zero, huh?

12:37.524 --> 12:39.592
How about you read a book?

12:42.762 --> 12:43.964
I'll be back tomorrow.

12:44.064 --> 12:46.232
Huh?
We'll do something.

12:46.233 --> 12:48.768
When do I get to meet him?

12:48.869 --> 12:50.637
- Him who?
- Your partner.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.172
[teapot clatters softly]

12:52.272 --> 12:54.507
You don't need
to meet men like him.

12:55.442 --> 12:56.977
He's that bad?

12:58.745 --> 13:00.747
When you lay down with dogs,
Banner,

13:00.848 --> 13:02.382
you stand up with fleas.

13:02.482 --> 13:03.650
[cup clatters softly]

13:04.484 --> 13:07.387
All our lives,
we've had nothing.

13:07.487 --> 13:09.555
Now we have something.

13:09.556 --> 13:12.359
And it ain't fleas.

13:13.961 --> 13:15.328
We have money.

13:15.428 --> 13:17.297
Soon we'll have land.

13:17.397 --> 13:20.133
And that boy will have a future.

13:27.074 --> 13:29.877
I'll lay with the devil
to give him that.

13:32.812 --> 13:34.080
[door closes]

13:34.081 --> 13:35.983
<i>♪ contemplative music ♪</i>

13:36.249 --> 13:38.451
<i>***</i>

13:53.033 --> 13:54.734
[coal rustles]

13:57.537 --> 14:00.273
Don't feed it too much.

14:01.374 --> 14:04.044
Don't feed?
What do I feed?

14:04.144 --> 14:06.646
You put too much coal.

14:06.746 --> 14:08.814
Pipe gets too hot,
it expands and blows.

14:08.815 --> 14:11.451
Then we die.
The ship sinks.

14:11.551 --> 14:12.685
I put too much?

14:12.819 --> 14:14.922
You are putting too much.

14:17.357 --> 14:18.790
What is this "feed"?

14:18.791 --> 14:20.993
Feed is food, no?
To eat?

14:20.994 --> 14:22.429
Yes.

14:23.296 --> 14:24.497
And the boiler

14:24.597 --> 14:26.066
is eating too much.

14:26.199 --> 14:27.000
Ah.

14:27.100 --> 14:30.037
Okay, okay, I understand.

14:30.137 --> 14:33.840
You make a-a joke
with the words.

14:38.979 --> 14:40.914
<i>[speaks Italian]</i>

14:44.684 --> 14:46.886
[indistinct chatter]

14:58.165 --> 14:59.899
<i>♪ uneasy music ♪</i>

15:00.167 --> 15:02.535
<i>***</i>

15:16.249 --> 15:18.451
[muffled whimpering]

15:42.709 --> 15:44.477
[grunts softly]

15:45.512 --> 15:47.714
[whimpering continues]

15:52.119 --> 15:53.820
[pained moan]

15:54.954 --> 15:57.857
[grunting]

16:02.562 --> 16:04.331
<i>[speaks Italian]</i>

16:05.132 --> 16:07.634
- [grunting]
- [sobbing]

16:08.968 --> 16:10.837
[grunting]

16:20.480 --> 16:21.814
Go back to your bunk

16:21.914 --> 16:23.550
before I do something
you can't walk away from.

16:24.417 --> 16:25.585
[panting]

16:25.685 --> 16:26.886
[pained grunt]

16:30.357 --> 16:32.125
Are you okay?

16:33.760 --> 16:36.496
[panting] He's standing up.

16:41.368 --> 16:43.002
[Spencer]
You come at me

16:43.103 --> 16:44.636
with that knife

16:44.637 --> 16:46.539
and I'm gonna
fucking kill you with it.

16:50.977 --> 16:52.611
[yells]

16:52.612 --> 16:54.981
[grunting]

17:10.697 --> 17:13.300
Stop it. Stop it. Stop it!

17:14.267 --> 17:16.669
Drop the belt. Now.

17:22.975 --> 17:24.611
He was raping him.

17:26.979 --> 17:28.948
Is true?

17:29.849 --> 17:31.751
[sobs quietly]

17:39.526 --> 17:41.428
<i>[speaking Italian]</i>

17:42.562 --> 17:44.864
It is not your ship to police.

17:44.964 --> 17:46.266
You see crime, you come to me.

17:46.366 --> 17:48.601
It is my ship to police.

17:50.069 --> 17:51.471
Clean it up.

17:52.839 --> 17:55.608
But do it in the dark.
The men need to sleep.

17:56.543 --> 17:57.509
[door shuts]

17:57.510 --> 17:59.479
[sobbing]

18:09.822 --> 18:12.792
[whimpering]

18:21.468 --> 18:23.270
<i>♪ ominous music ♪</i>

18:23.536 --> 18:25.672
<i>***</i>

18:26.439 --> 18:28.575
[indistinct chatter]

18:35.148 --> 18:36.849
[whoops]

18:42.222 --> 18:45.057
- They got rifles.
- I see them.

18:45.158 --> 18:46.993
Put down your weapons.

18:48.295 --> 18:50.497
Drop your rifles to the ground.

18:53.333 --> 18:56.636
- Lower your rifle.
- What you want here?

18:56.736 --> 18:59.472
- I will not ask again.
- What you want here?

19:02.041 --> 19:04.311
[screaming]

19:07.013 --> 19:08.981
[people shouting, crying]

19:21.628 --> 19:24.063
[exclaiming]

19:25.198 --> 19:26.866
[Kent]
I am looking for

19:26.999 --> 19:29.001
a Crow, Indian girl,

19:29.101 --> 19:30.769
16 years old.

19:30.770 --> 19:32.705
Have you seen her?

19:36.108 --> 19:37.577
[gasps]

19:42.048 --> 19:44.951
- [exclaiming]
- Aah!

19:45.818 --> 19:48.620
Crow! Indian girl.

19:48.621 --> 19:49.756
Sixteen years old.

19:49.856 --> 19:51.156
Have you seen her?

19:51.157 --> 19:52.892
There are no Crow here.

19:53.025 --> 19:55.961
- There are no Crow.
- [Renaud] Marshal!

19:55.962 --> 20:00.367
As a man of God,
I demand you release this child.

20:01.167 --> 20:03.603
- Oh, you demand it, huh?
- I do.

20:08.808 --> 20:10.309
[women exclaiming, sighing]

20:10.310 --> 20:12.545
I seen your graveyard, Father.

20:12.645 --> 20:16.249
That same man of God
staring at me now--

20:16.383 --> 20:18.217
that's the one who filled it.

20:18.318 --> 20:20.052
[grunts]

20:20.152 --> 20:22.121
God's will filled it.

20:23.189 --> 20:24.891
Now we're getting somewhere.

20:24.991 --> 20:27.460
That's what I am.
The will of God.

20:27.560 --> 20:28.595
Hyah!

20:28.728 --> 20:30.630
Hyah! Hyah!

20:32.732 --> 20:34.901
[people exclaiming, shouting]

20:38.605 --> 20:40.507
You tell every Comanche

20:40.607 --> 20:42.609
I'm looking for this Crow!

20:42.709 --> 20:44.744
Not gonna stop till we find her.

20:44.844 --> 20:47.514
Better for your families
if you help us.

20:47.614 --> 20:49.282
Hyah. Hyah!

20:49.416 --> 20:50.950
Go.

21:11.237 --> 21:13.005
<i>♪ somber music ♪</i>

21:13.272 --> 21:15.475
<i>***</i>

21:46.339 --> 21:47.907
Huh.

22:04.056 --> 22:06.192
I watched my grandfather.

22:07.059 --> 22:08.093
There was a time

22:08.094 --> 22:09.496
when everything was crafted

22:09.596 --> 22:11.464
from the earth.

22:12.432 --> 22:14.834
And everyone knew how to do it.

22:14.934 --> 22:17.670
Why don't we know it anymore?
What happened?

22:17.770 --> 22:19.539
White man happened.

22:21.140 --> 22:23.843
The white man, he comes and
he trades with us

22:23.943 --> 22:25.445
for our skins,

22:25.545 --> 22:28.447
our horses and our beads.

22:28.448 --> 22:31.350
He gives us sugar, knives,

22:31.484 --> 22:32.618
- [arrow thunks]
- iron.

22:32.619 --> 22:34.220
Then the people

22:34.353 --> 22:36.355
who want to craft things
from the land--

22:36.456 --> 22:37.890
they want to trade
for the things

22:37.990 --> 22:40.359
that make life easy.

22:40.493 --> 22:42.794
And then when we run
out of things to trade,

22:42.795 --> 22:45.665
the government
just gives us the things

22:45.765 --> 22:48.500
till we forget how to make
the things ourselves.

22:48.501 --> 22:50.301
Now they have our land.

22:50.302 --> 22:52.038
We're beggars at their fort.

22:53.673 --> 22:55.442
That's what governments want.

22:55.542 --> 22:57.143
They want beggars.

22:57.243 --> 22:59.145
Why would they want that?

22:59.245 --> 23:00.747
Because beggars--

23:00.880 --> 23:03.583
they cannot question.

23:03.683 --> 23:06.886
A beggar who question
goes hungry.

23:07.887 --> 23:10.256
A beggar who questions
gets sent off to schools

23:10.356 --> 23:12.658
and taught not to question.

23:12.659 --> 23:14.761
Better we don't beg at all.

23:15.662 --> 23:16.862
Better to just

23:16.863 --> 23:19.799
do things for yourself.

23:19.899 --> 23:22.268
Till the government
finds out you're doing it.

23:23.069 --> 23:24.437
Well, what does
the government care?

23:24.571 --> 23:27.607
Because if we're doing things
for ourself...

23:28.741 --> 23:31.010
...then we don't
need a government.

23:32.479 --> 23:34.212
[Pete] I'm gonna slip down
to the river,

23:34.213 --> 23:36.616
see if I can catch
a deer crossing.

23:42.021 --> 23:44.557
<i>♪ pastoral music ♪</i>

23:44.657 --> 23:46.025
He's a good boy.

23:46.926 --> 23:48.628
I think so.

23:57.604 --> 23:59.338
You want his hand?

24:02.909 --> 24:04.711
If you want him to have it...

24:06.445 --> 24:09.215
...give him permission
to ask for it.

24:16.088 --> 24:18.224
I want him to have it.

24:19.692 --> 24:21.127
Have you two...

24:21.994 --> 24:23.329
What?

24:23.462 --> 24:24.831
You know what.

24:24.931 --> 24:26.899
When would we do that?

24:26.999 --> 24:29.235
You watch us like the hawk.

24:30.469 --> 24:32.872
Wait till after the ceremony.

24:33.005 --> 24:35.074
When's the ceremony?

24:36.142 --> 24:37.610
[exclaims quietly]

24:37.710 --> 24:40.278
By the looks of it,
it better be quick. [exclaims]

24:40.279 --> 24:42.582
Well, did you wait
for the ceremony?

24:43.482 --> 24:45.051
[sighs]

24:45.184 --> 24:47.554
Nobody waits for the ceremony.

24:47.654 --> 24:49.922
Just have to say it.

24:55.494 --> 24:57.263
I think I'm...

24:57.363 --> 24:59.464
I'm just gonna go sit by Pete

24:59.465 --> 25:01.901
while he... while he hunts.

25:05.938 --> 25:07.907
[Runs His Horse] Mm-hmm.

25:13.479 --> 25:14.914
[quiet rustling]

25:43.075 --> 25:45.010
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

25:45.011 --> 25:47.780
<i>***</i>

26:07.099 --> 26:09.335
<i>***</i>

26:16.375 --> 26:17.977
[chuckles softly]

26:37.463 --> 26:39.699
<i>***</i>

27:01.587 --> 27:03.756
<i>***</i>

27:09.061 --> 27:10.797
[chuckles]

27:11.998 --> 27:13.733
[chuckles]

27:35.354 --> 27:37.589
<i>***</i>

27:45.497 --> 27:47.266
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

27:47.533 --> 27:49.535
<i>***</i>

27:53.339 --> 27:54.841
Shh, shh.

28:04.884 --> 28:07.086
<i>***</i>

28:34.380 --> 28:35.547
Ho!

28:37.950 --> 28:39.684
Dang.

28:39.685 --> 28:41.487
You scared the life out of me.

28:44.290 --> 28:46.292
Hunting you some deer?

28:47.426 --> 28:48.460
Trying to.

28:48.594 --> 28:50.729
Sorry to screw it up for you.

28:51.530 --> 28:54.032
Still early. Deer won't mind
that horse's scent.

28:54.033 --> 28:56.602
They'll mind mine,
and I got plenty of it.

28:56.735 --> 28:59.205
Haven't seen any cattle sign
on the river, have you?

28:59.305 --> 29:00.472
I'm prowling for strays.

29:00.606 --> 29:02.641
Haven't seen any cattle.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.310
Once they get down
in this canyon,

29:04.443 --> 29:06.112
they get wilder than the deer.

29:06.212 --> 29:08.147
You'll see the sign
before you see the cattle.

29:08.280 --> 29:09.748
Haven't seen any sign.

29:09.849 --> 29:11.884
- Comanche let you graze here?
- Comanche?

29:11.984 --> 29:13.752
Only Comanche in these parts
looks to be you.

29:13.853 --> 29:15.887
Thought this canyon
was Comanche land.

29:15.888 --> 29:18.057
It was.
That's been a while, though.

29:18.157 --> 29:19.792
Before my time.

29:19.926 --> 29:21.560
Comanche are all
up north of Vernon.

29:21.660 --> 29:25.631
No, you're smack-dab in the
bottom of the JA Ranch in Texas.

29:25.764 --> 29:26.799
Texas?

29:26.933 --> 29:28.634
You missed Oklahoma
by 100 miles.

29:28.734 --> 29:30.502
- Oh.
- Should've turned left

29:30.636 --> 29:31.971
at the river, not followed it.

29:32.071 --> 29:33.305
Don't worry none.

29:33.405 --> 29:34.807
You ain't minding nobody.

29:34.941 --> 29:37.608
Mr. Goodnight was a good friend
of Quanah Parker's.

29:37.609 --> 29:39.145
And Mr. Goodnight
never refused a Comanche

29:39.278 --> 29:41.013
come camp his old grounds.

29:43.349 --> 29:44.917
Best get moving.
Don't want to

29:45.017 --> 29:46.352
spend the night in this canyon.

29:46.452 --> 29:47.854
It's a rattlesnake factory.

29:47.987 --> 29:50.823
There may be a couple more
punchers riding this way,

29:50.957 --> 29:53.091
but they won't mess
with you none.

29:53.092 --> 29:54.894
<i>♪ serene music ♪</i>

29:55.161 --> 29:57.363
<i>***</i>

30:05.972 --> 30:07.073
We're in Texas.

30:07.173 --> 30:09.008
Texas?

30:09.108 --> 30:10.475
- On a ranch.
- [chuckles]

30:10.476 --> 30:12.344
Don't look like
much of a ranch to me.

30:12.478 --> 30:15.581
Me neither,
but that's what it is.

30:16.348 --> 30:18.650
Do you think he'll tell people
we're here?

30:18.750 --> 30:20.719
I don't think
there's anyone to tell.

30:20.819 --> 30:22.288
Didn't seem to mind.

30:22.388 --> 30:23.454
He's pretty friendly.

30:23.455 --> 30:25.490
- Friendly?
- Yeah.

30:25.491 --> 30:27.927
Even apologized
for messing up my hunt.

30:29.595 --> 30:31.497
I didn't tell him
who really messed up my hunt.

30:33.365 --> 30:35.935
[chuckling softly]

30:39.538 --> 30:42.875
Maybe we should go back and...

30:42.975 --> 30:44.410
tell my father.

30:44.543 --> 30:46.778
We should, but we ain't gonna.

30:49.048 --> 30:50.616
Not yet.

31:17.009 --> 31:19.211
<i>***</i>

31:34.961 --> 31:36.262
[Alex]
Go away.

31:36.395 --> 31:38.230
Alex, it's me.

31:40.632 --> 31:42.101
Alex?

31:42.935 --> 31:44.736
You go away as well.

31:44.836 --> 31:46.305
I will not.

31:48.307 --> 31:49.841
[scoffs]

31:54.546 --> 31:55.747
[clicks tongue]

31:56.815 --> 31:59.051
[grunts]

32:10.862 --> 32:12.664
<i>♪ mournful music ♪</i>

32:12.999 --> 32:15.134
<i>***</i>

32:29.982 --> 32:33.252
My God, Alex,
you're withering away.

32:34.320 --> 32:36.255
Yes, I am.

32:36.355 --> 32:38.957
Are you ill?

32:40.059 --> 32:42.028
I'm broken, Jennifer.

32:42.828 --> 32:45.564
If you're ill,
you should see a doctor.

32:46.665 --> 32:48.667
Do you think
a doctor will prescribe me

32:48.767 --> 32:50.436
a ticket to America?

32:55.307 --> 32:57.843
If he loves you,
he'll come for you.

32:57.943 --> 33:00.812
He can't come for me.
He must protect his family.

33:00.912 --> 33:02.881
Protect them from what--

33:03.015 --> 33:05.051
from bears?

33:05.151 --> 33:08.287
I will not have
this conversation with you.

33:14.226 --> 33:16.562
I need passage to America.

33:18.030 --> 33:20.399
I'm running out of time.

33:20.499 --> 33:22.101
And I have no means.

33:22.201 --> 33:23.735
No money.

33:23.835 --> 33:26.905
No family or friends
who will help me.

33:27.906 --> 33:32.177
Time is the one thing
you do have, Alex.

33:32.178 --> 33:34.080
In abundance.

33:35.181 --> 33:36.982
Be patient.

33:37.083 --> 33:40.586
Perhaps he will send for you
when he reaches Montana.

33:59.571 --> 34:01.807
I'm running out of time.

34:03.642 --> 34:05.411
You're pregnant?

34:06.278 --> 34:07.879
- Mm-hmm.
- [gasps]

34:07.979 --> 34:10.515
[both chuckling]

34:10.516 --> 34:14.019
[sobbing]

34:17.756 --> 34:20.292
When I begin to show, what then?

34:21.427 --> 34:23.861
What will Arthur
do to my family then?

34:23.862 --> 34:27.099
He's already banned them
from London.

34:30.269 --> 34:33.339
I belong with my husband.

34:35.207 --> 34:37.708
His child belongs
with his father.

34:37.709 --> 34:40.212
Oh, Alex.

34:42.514 --> 34:44.483
You claim to be my best friend.

34:44.583 --> 34:47.018
I more than claim it.

34:49.355 --> 34:51.990
Now is your chance to prove it.

34:54.025 --> 34:55.461
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

34:55.727 --> 34:58.297
<i>***</i>

35:05.671 --> 35:07.438
Sell these.

35:07.439 --> 35:10.309
Buy me passage
and bring me to London.

35:10.409 --> 35:12.378
Alex, some of these
belong with the estate,

35:12.478 --> 35:13.745
some belong with the court.

35:13.845 --> 35:16.682
You could go to prison
and so could I.

35:16.815 --> 35:20.252
I never said proving it
would be easy.

35:21.387 --> 35:22.688
Sell them in Brighton.

35:22.821 --> 35:24.556
They'll offer a pittance
for what they're worth.

35:24.656 --> 35:26.192
Take it.

35:26.292 --> 35:29.695
Tell my parents I've agreed
to stay in Oxford with you.

35:29.828 --> 35:32.198
Tell them it would be good
for me to see friends

35:32.298 --> 35:33.865
and be around young men
with stature

35:33.965 --> 35:36.101
and a future ahead of them.

35:41.307 --> 35:44.476
That's what a best friend
would do.

35:46.111 --> 35:48.380
Then that's what shall be done.

35:49.215 --> 35:50.682
[laughs softly]

35:52.351 --> 35:54.052
[sniffles]

35:54.186 --> 35:55.587
[both laugh softly]

35:58.990 --> 36:01.527
Book passage on the first ship
heading west.

36:01.627 --> 36:04.963
Not the poshest ship.
The first.

36:05.063 --> 36:07.333
And book me second class.

36:07.433 --> 36:10.035
I don't need to be housed
beside Arthur's classmates

36:10.135 --> 36:13.739
- heading to New York.
- Second class, Alex?

36:13.872 --> 36:15.673
Gamblers and thieves.

36:15.674 --> 36:17.042
And without a man beside you...

36:17.175 --> 36:19.411
I can take care of myself.

36:24.283 --> 36:26.285
- Go.
- Mm.

36:43.869 --> 36:45.304
[drawer opens]

37:01.219 --> 37:05.557
[Alex]
<i>Spencer. My love. My life.</i>

37:05.657 --> 37:07.393
<i>I know not the path
nor the manner</i>

37:07.493 --> 37:10.095
<i>with which I will find
my way to you.</i>

37:11.062 --> 37:13.198
<i>But it is time
the journey begin.</i>

37:14.466 --> 37:16.167
<i>I will enter the port
in New York</i>

37:16.268 --> 37:19.838
<i>and then seek passage by train
to Montana.</i>

37:43.395 --> 37:45.564
<i>***</i>

38:09.588 --> 38:11.757
<i>***</i>

38:30.976 --> 38:32.744
Seen a lot of men do it.

38:33.779 --> 38:35.747
Never like this, though.

38:38.850 --> 38:41.319
Most do it quick, with a bullet.

38:42.187 --> 38:43.989
I don't have a gun.

38:44.089 --> 38:46.091
Can you swim?

38:47.025 --> 38:48.694
I can swim.

38:54.199 --> 38:56.267
That's gonna be a problem.

38:57.403 --> 38:59.204
Why is that a problem?

38:59.304 --> 39:01.507
You may want to die,
but your body don't.

39:01.607 --> 39:03.241
Your body will fight.

39:03.341 --> 39:05.976
And then you'll tread water
till you can't.

39:05.977 --> 39:07.713
Then you'll float.

39:08.514 --> 39:10.248
It's a pretty smooth day.

39:10.348 --> 39:12.418
Yesterday was the day to jump.

39:14.085 --> 39:16.855
So, if you jump in,
be ready for a long day.

39:16.955 --> 39:20.258
I will just go under,

39:20.358 --> 39:22.928
open my mouth and...

39:23.061 --> 39:24.262
breathe deep.

39:24.362 --> 39:25.731
Yeah, but your body
won't let you.

39:25.864 --> 39:28.867
You'll just sit here
and float till a storm

39:28.967 --> 39:30.936
or a shark has its way with you.

39:37.242 --> 39:40.078
How long has he been
doing that to you?

39:41.913 --> 39:44.082
Since we left port.

39:44.182 --> 39:46.585
<i>♪ melancholy music ♪</i>

39:46.852 --> 39:49.353
<i>***</i>

39:49.354 --> 39:52.090
People aren't defined
by what happens to them.

39:52.190 --> 39:53.825
They're defined by what they do.

39:54.993 --> 39:57.695
More often than not, they're
defined by what they don't do.

39:57.696 --> 39:59.965
What they're too scared to do.

40:00.065 --> 40:02.333
Too lazy or selfish.

40:04.135 --> 40:05.604
Is your mother alive?

40:12.944 --> 40:14.345
Does she love you?

40:16.548 --> 40:18.283
Of course.

40:18.383 --> 40:20.752
You're just gonna
throw that over the side?

40:22.087 --> 40:24.055
I wrote her a letter.

40:27.659 --> 40:29.194
These?

40:32.330 --> 40:33.832
No address on it.

40:35.066 --> 40:36.134
I wrote two letters.

40:36.234 --> 40:38.904
O-One... one is to you.

40:39.004 --> 40:40.271
It's in Italian.

40:40.371 --> 40:41.873
Can't read Italian.

40:41.973 --> 40:43.775
Don't know to write English.

40:45.677 --> 40:47.012
Read it.

40:52.584 --> 40:55.587
Thank you for saving me

40:55.687 --> 40:57.155
from the big man.

40:57.288 --> 40:59.591
For fighting him.

41:00.759 --> 41:03.929
I wish God made me big,

41:04.029 --> 41:06.197
but He didn't.

41:08.133 --> 41:10.100
In Galveston,
ask for my cousins,

41:10.101 --> 41:12.538
Salvatore and Rosario Maceo.

41:13.371 --> 41:14.506
Galveston is their city.

41:14.640 --> 41:16.875
Give them both letters.

41:18.510 --> 41:20.879
They will pay you for saving me.

41:22.013 --> 41:24.583
But if you jump off this ship,
I didn't save you.

41:26.051 --> 41:27.385
Ah.

41:29.855 --> 41:32.023
Didn't think of that.

41:53.779 --> 41:55.180
Let's get back to work.

42:04.990 --> 42:07.158
<i>***</i>

42:11.029 --> 42:12.598
[shovel scraping]

42:35.921 --> 42:38.323
Why do men call you lion hunter?

42:39.190 --> 42:40.892
That's what I did.

42:40.992 --> 42:42.427
My grandfather said,

42:42.527 --> 42:45.195
when he was young,
there were lions in Italy.

42:45.196 --> 42:48.767
Two kinds: one with no mane
that live in the mountains,

42:48.867 --> 42:53.271
and, uh, the Barbary lions,
which lived near the farms

42:53.371 --> 42:55.874
and would eat the cattle
and horses.

42:59.611 --> 43:02.180
There's lions
in our mountains, too.

43:03.949 --> 43:05.684
They don't mess with the cattle.

43:05.784 --> 43:07.352
In America, there is lions?

43:07.452 --> 43:10.455
I would love to see a lion.

43:12.123 --> 43:13.959
I just want the lion
to never see me.

43:14.059 --> 43:16.828
Yeah, you do not want
the lion to see you.

43:21.332 --> 43:22.834
Italy's home for you?

43:23.769 --> 43:27.072
My family is from Palermo,
in Sicily.

43:27.172 --> 43:30.275
But, uh, with Mussolini...

43:31.376 --> 43:34.780
My mother sent me to Galveston
so I-I don't die in the war.

43:34.880 --> 43:37.748
- Didn't know there was a war.
- In Libya.

43:37.749 --> 43:41.386
Next will be Tunisia,
then Egypt, then Greece.

43:41.486 --> 43:45.190
- We just got done with our war.
- They starting a new one.

43:46.324 --> 43:49.394
There are two kind of men
in this world, I think.

43:49.494 --> 43:53.765
Men who make things
and the men who take them.

43:55.500 --> 43:58.870
Mussolini is a man who takes.

44:00.405 --> 44:02.973
- Where's home for you?
- In the mountains.

44:02.974 --> 44:04.474
In the north.

44:04.475 --> 44:08.079
- That is where you go?
- As soon as I have enough money.

44:11.182 --> 44:13.151
You could sell that big gun.

44:13.251 --> 44:15.020
Gonna need that big gun.

44:16.688 --> 44:18.489
You could fight for the money.

44:18.589 --> 44:20.025
- Don't fight for money.
- Lion hunting

44:20.125 --> 44:22.327
- is fighting, no?
- It's fighting for survival.

44:22.427 --> 44:24.462
Don't fight for sport.

44:25.931 --> 44:27.332
Why you go home?

44:30.736 --> 44:32.838
Family needs me.

44:32.938 --> 44:34.372
Why they need you so bad?
You work a ship's engine

44:34.472 --> 44:35.707
to give back to them.

44:35.807 --> 44:38.376
- They're in danger.
- Then fighting for money

44:38.476 --> 44:42.213
is for survival,
if the money gets you home.

44:42.313 --> 44:44.314
<i>♪ slow, contemplative music ♪</i>

44:44.315 --> 44:47.318
<i>***</i>

44:58.663 --> 44:59.898
Umbrellas.

44:59.998 --> 45:01.232
What about 'em?

45:01.332 --> 45:02.500
Umbrellas.
That's the word.

45:02.600 --> 45:04.402
Ain't the word anymore.

45:05.203 --> 45:07.072
Well, what's the password now?

45:07.172 --> 45:09.506
Wouldn't be much of a password
if I told it to you.

45:09.507 --> 45:12.744
Roy, open the fucking door.

45:12.878 --> 45:14.412
Yes, sir.

45:15.246 --> 45:17.514
<i>[lively music playing]</i>

45:17.515 --> 45:19.516
<i>***</i>

45:19.517 --> 45:21.820
[indistinct chatter]

45:27.793 --> 45:29.160
Ooh.

45:30.095 --> 45:31.361
Hey.

45:31.362 --> 45:34.032
Marshal out of Helena called

45:34.132 --> 45:36.101
and said they got
an anonymous tip

45:36.201 --> 45:38.636
that there's a speakeasy
off of Main street.

45:38.770 --> 45:40.271
You don't say.

45:41.139 --> 45:42.373
Yep.

45:43.208 --> 45:45.476
You have any luck finding it?

45:45.610 --> 45:47.946
Investigation's
just getting started.

45:48.046 --> 45:49.714
These things take a while.

45:49.815 --> 45:51.850
Another whiskey, Charlie.

45:58.089 --> 45:59.825
[Charlie]
Takes away the bite.

45:59.925 --> 46:02.160
Well, don't take away
all the bite.

46:04.262 --> 46:05.296
Who's the judge?

46:05.396 --> 46:06.596
Garrett.

46:06.597 --> 46:07.731
Oh.

46:07.732 --> 46:09.734
He's married to that Crow woman.

46:11.069 --> 46:12.670
I don't get it.
I mean, how is it

46:12.770 --> 46:16.207
illegal to marry into one race
and not another?

46:16.307 --> 46:17.809
Well, it all depended
on the race

46:17.943 --> 46:19.510
of the legislators' wives
when they

46:19.644 --> 46:21.046
drew up the law
in the first place.

46:21.146 --> 46:22.313
Yeah.

46:22.413 --> 46:24.414
It was almost illegal
to marry a Mexican

46:24.415 --> 46:26.151
till a senator
met a little senorita

46:26.251 --> 46:27.685
on a hunting trip in Texas.

46:27.819 --> 46:30.055
How much trouble are they in?

46:30.155 --> 46:31.756
Well, the marriage is void.

46:32.858 --> 46:34.591
And the preacher
who performed the marriage--

46:34.592 --> 46:36.594
he can go to jail.

46:36.694 --> 46:38.963
But Zane's wife
won't say who that was.

46:38.964 --> 46:40.698
And that's really
what this is all about.

46:40.798 --> 46:43.234
She refuses
to divulge the source.

46:43.334 --> 46:44.836
She's gonna be held in contempt.

46:44.936 --> 46:46.604
Back to jail she goes.

46:47.805 --> 46:49.307
You seen Zane?

46:49.407 --> 46:51.076
He ain't any better.

46:51.943 --> 46:53.310
Is he talking?

46:53.311 --> 46:55.713
They got him
walking the halls in there

46:55.813 --> 46:57.281
and they won't let him
see his wife,

46:57.282 --> 46:59.017
won't let him see his kids.

46:59.117 --> 47:02.087
I swear it's a broken heart
more than it is his head.

47:05.023 --> 47:06.892
It's that fucking Whitfield.

47:07.725 --> 47:09.227
I know it is.

47:10.028 --> 47:13.298
He's gonna knock all
your chess pieces off the board.

47:14.132 --> 47:15.299
Get those taxes paid.

47:15.300 --> 47:16.902
Yeah, I got last year's paid.

47:17.002 --> 47:18.836
It's just next year
I ain't figured.

47:18.937 --> 47:20.271
Well, you better
figure 'em out quick,

47:20.371 --> 47:21.972
'cause I can promise you
that son of a bitch

47:21.973 --> 47:23.909
has got it figured.

47:27.345 --> 47:29.547
[indistinct chatter]

47:36.888 --> 47:38.890
You think you can take him?

47:40.025 --> 47:41.626
[Spencer]
Are there rules?

47:41.726 --> 47:42.659
- Rules?
- To the fight.

47:42.660 --> 47:43.693
Are there any rules?

47:43.694 --> 47:44.861
Can you bite?

47:44.862 --> 47:46.097
Can you kick?

47:46.197 --> 47:47.732
You can do anything.
It's a fight.

47:47.832 --> 47:49.334
Then yes.

47:49.434 --> 47:50.768
Big guys are

47:50.902 --> 47:52.303
easy to beat as long as they
don't get a hold of you.

47:52.403 --> 47:54.605
Then let's start with him.

47:55.473 --> 47:57.308
Wait, wait, kid.

48:00.645 --> 48:02.880
[indistinct conversation]

48:14.292 --> 48:16.627
<i>♪ energetic music ♪</i>

48:16.962 --> 48:18.964
<i>***</i>

48:19.064 --> 48:21.466
[indistinct chatter]

48:27.138 --> 48:29.206
Okay.

48:29.207 --> 48:30.741
One round.

48:30.841 --> 48:33.144
No time limit, no rules.

48:33.278 --> 48:35.379
The man who cannot get up

48:35.380 --> 48:37.682
or will not get up is the loser.

48:38.616 --> 48:41.119
<i>- Pronto?
- Si.</i>

48:41.987 --> 48:43.121
Ready?

48:43.221 --> 48:44.289
Step to your left.

48:44.422 --> 48:45.390
Fight!

48:45.490 --> 48:47.125
- [grunting]
- [men exclaiming]

48:55.133 --> 48:57.835
[cheering]

48:59.270 --> 49:00.838
I'm really glad you won.

49:00.972 --> 49:02.540
I don't have any money either.

49:03.441 --> 49:04.709
Okay.
<i>[speaking Italian]</i>

49:14.752 --> 49:15.752
You fought in the war?

49:15.753 --> 49:17.655
- Yep.
- Kill many Germans?

49:17.755 --> 49:18.956
Every one I could find.

49:19.057 --> 49:20.257
[chuckles]

49:20.258 --> 49:21.426
Me too.

49:21.526 --> 49:23.828
No gouging eyes, okay?

49:23.928 --> 49:26.164
A blind man
cannot work on ships.

49:26.297 --> 49:27.764
No gouging eyes.

49:27.765 --> 49:29.667
- [grunting]
- [clamoring]

49:34.139 --> 49:36.241
[shouting]

49:48.153 --> 49:49.354
[yelping]

49:49.487 --> 49:51.955
[shouts]

49:51.956 --> 49:53.858
[spits]

49:53.991 --> 49:56.194
[shouts]

50:14.645 --> 50:16.881
[clamoring stops]

50:17.014 --> 50:19.150
[panting]

50:23.054 --> 50:25.056
[cheering]

50:31.729 --> 50:34.432
[indistinct chatter]

50:35.666 --> 50:37.735
<i>♪ somber music ♪</i>

50:38.002 --> 50:40.138
<i>***</i>

50:40.238 --> 50:44.342
Four hundred and twenty dollars.

50:45.443 --> 50:47.912
You can buy a new Model T

50:48.012 --> 50:50.915
and still have money left over.

50:55.653 --> 50:56.987
What are you doing?

50:58.156 --> 51:00.591
Twenty percent,
for covering the bets.

51:00.691 --> 51:03.261
But you didn't cover any bets.
You don't have any money.

51:03.361 --> 51:05.430
I took the risk of lying.

51:05.530 --> 51:07.565
All you had to do
is fight one man at a time.

51:07.665 --> 51:10.101
I would have been beaten
by the whole room.

51:10.201 --> 51:12.002
Now I have money
to cover more bets

51:12.103 --> 51:15.140
and you have the money
to get home. Mm?

51:24.048 --> 51:26.216
Unless...

51:26.217 --> 51:29.287
they try and steal it
from us while we're sleeping.

51:32.623 --> 51:34.424
<i>Buona notte.</i>

51:34.425 --> 51:36.294
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

51:36.561 --> 51:38.729
<i>***</i>

52:00.318 --> 52:02.520
<i>***</i>

52:18.269 --> 52:20.270
[bell ringing]

52:20.271 --> 52:22.640
<i>[man shouting in Italian]</i>

52:24.041 --> 52:26.244
[ship horn blows]

52:36.854 --> 52:39.056
Second class was sold out.

52:39.156 --> 52:42.360
It was first class
or tourist class.

52:43.194 --> 52:45.563
I'll take my chances
with the tourists.

52:45.663 --> 52:47.064
They aren't tourists, Alex.

52:47.198 --> 52:49.234
They only call it that
because they can't call it

52:49.334 --> 52:51.369
the thieves and beggars class.

52:52.270 --> 52:53.871
Thought there'd be more.

52:54.004 --> 52:56.139
No one of good repute
would trade with me.

52:56.140 --> 52:58.576
I was forced to the alleys.

52:58.676 --> 53:00.511
And alley prices
is what they brought.

53:08.886 --> 53:11.789
I wonder if it's colder
in Montana.

53:12.957 --> 53:15.560
Can't be any colder than this.
[chuckles]

53:26.737 --> 53:29.106
I'm hoping
you'll send it back to me.

53:30.074 --> 53:32.443
But if you don't...

53:33.411 --> 53:35.780
...I'll know you needed it.

53:40.184 --> 53:42.119
You've proved it.

53:44.255 --> 53:46.691
I long for the day
when I can return the favor.

53:46.791 --> 53:47.758
Hmm?

53:47.892 --> 53:49.294
[short chuckle]

53:53.230 --> 53:55.333
- [giggles softly]
- [ship horn blows]

54:03.741 --> 54:05.710
I'm off on the next adventure.

54:05.810 --> 54:07.845
[both laugh]

54:17.922 --> 54:20.124
[ship horn blows]

54:42.279 --> 54:45.850
- That's new.
- Yeah.

54:46.617 --> 54:47.752
[Jack]
Know how they work?

54:47.852 --> 54:49.654
I got no idea.

54:50.621 --> 54:52.423
Well, you got someone
you need to call?

54:53.758 --> 54:54.692
Yes, I do.

54:54.792 --> 54:56.661
Very much.

55:01.131 --> 55:02.867
<i>♪ serene music ♪</i>

55:03.200 --> 55:05.169
<i>***</i>

55:15.946 --> 55:17.348
[sighs]

55:18.282 --> 55:19.384
At last.

55:19.484 --> 55:22.387
I'd forgotten
what the sun looks like.

55:28.793 --> 55:32.296
I'm not sure why I'm making
all these eggs.

55:33.063 --> 55:35.900
Maybe I should send some
down to the cowboys.

55:42.773 --> 55:45.710
Elizabeth, breakfast is ready.

55:45.843 --> 55:47.745
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

55:48.012 --> 55:50.047
<i>***</i>

55:50.180 --> 55:52.383
[low growling]

55:58.523 --> 55:59.524
[gunshot]

56:04.729 --> 56:06.063
[panting]

56:14.204 --> 56:16.707
I thought that thing
was gonna eat me alive.

56:16.807 --> 56:19.209
It was its plan.

56:20.010 --> 56:22.780
[Elsa]
<i>Winter is the killing season.</i>

56:22.913 --> 56:26.016
<i>When the hunters among us
seek out the weak, the foolish.</i>

56:26.116 --> 56:28.453
<i>Only the very strongest</i>

56:28.586 --> 56:30.621
<i>of nature's creatures
survive it.</i>

56:32.222 --> 56:33.891
<i>Winter is the time of the wolf.</i>

56:33.991 --> 56:35.292
<i>The time of the lion.</i>

56:35.392 --> 56:37.327
<i>When all nature's failures</i>

56:37.428 --> 56:39.597
<i>become a meal.</i>

56:40.397 --> 56:42.366
<i>Then spring brings new life.</i>

56:42.467 --> 56:44.134
<i>And God tries again.</i>

56:44.935 --> 56:47.738
[wolf howls in distance]

56:52.910 --> 56:55.680
[wolves howling in distance]

57:08.559 --> 57:10.761
<i>***</i>
